p.said:
Socrates. Let us, my good friend, investigate in common, and if you can contradict anything I say, do so, and I will yield to your arguments; 
but if you cannot, my dear friend, stop at once saying the same thing to me over and over, that I ought to go away from here without the consent of the Athenians;  for I am anxious to act in this matter with your approval, and not contrary to your wishes.  Now see if the beginning of the investigation satisfies you, and try to reply
to my questions to the best of your belief.
